# Privacy Policy

**App Name:** Hydrio  
**Effective Date:** March 18, 2026  
**Last Updated:** March 18, 2026

---

## 1. Overview

Hydrio ("we", "our", or "the app") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use Hydrio on your iOS device.

**Short version:** Hydrio does not collect, transmit, or share any personal data with us or any third party. Everything stays on your device.

---

## 2. Information We Collect

### 2.1 Data You Provide (Stored Locally Only)
Hydrio stores the following data **exclusively on your device**:

| Data | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| Name, weight, gender | Personalized hydration goal calculation |
| Activity level | Adjust recommended daily intake |
| Drink logs (amount, type, time) | Track hydration history |
| Daily hydration goals | Progress tracking |
| Streaks and achievements | Gamification and motivation |
| Pet progression data | In-app virtual pet feature |
| Reminder preferences | Local notification scheduling |

**None of this data is transmitted to any server.** Hydrio has no backend, no user accounts, and no cloud sync.

### 2.2 Data We Do NOT Collect
- ❌ Personal identifiers (email, phone number, Apple ID)
- ❌ Analytics, crash reports, or usage statistics
- ❌ Location data
- ❌ Camera, microphone, or contacts
- ❌ Advertising identifiers (IDFA)
- ❌ Any biometric data

---

## 3. Notifications

If you enable hydration reminders during onboarding or in Settings, Hydrio uses **Apple's local notification system**. These notifications are:

- Generated and delivered entirely **on-device** — no push notification servers involved
- Available at intervals of 30 minutes, 1 hour, or 2 hours (as configured by you)
- Fully controllable via **iOS Settings → Notifications → Hydrio**

You can disable or modify notifications at any time without affecting your hydration data.

